3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses improving the training process for a compressed U-net, which is relevant to the broader field of AI. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses regularization methods, which are commonly used in neural networks. 
5. cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the compressed U-net.
